10 Section 2. KRS 313.021 is amended to read as follows:
11 (1) The board shall:
12 (a) Exercise all of the administrative functions of the Commonwealth in the
13 regulation of the profession of dentistry, including but not limited to dentists,
14 dental hygienists, dental assistants, and dental laboratories;
15 (b) Subject to the provisions of this chapter, create levels of licensure or
16 registration as appropriate for individuals providing services under this
17 chapter. These shall consist of:
18 1. Dentist;
19 2. Dental hygienist; and
20 3. Dental assistant;
21 (c) [The board shall ]Promulgate administrative regulations in accordance with
22 KRS Chapter 13A for any license or registration the board may create. The
23 administrative regulations shall, at a minimum, address:
24 1. Requirements for students, if appropriate;
25 2. Requirements for education;
26 3. Eligibility for licensure or registration; and
27 4. Renewal requirements;
