1 (d) Oversee the operations and establish the organizational structure of the Office
2 of the Kentucky Board of Dentistry, which is created and shall be attached to
3 the board for administrative purposes. The office shall be headed by the
4 executive director appointed under paragraph (e) of this subsection and shall
5 be responsible for:
6 1. Personnel and budget matters affecting the board;
7 2. Fiscal activities of the board, including grant writing and disbursement
8 of funds;
9 3. Information technology, including the design and maintenance of
10 databases;
11 4. Licensure of dentists and dental hygienists;
12 5. Registration of dental assistants;
13 6. Investigation of complaints; and
14 7. Other responsibilities which may be assigned to the executive director
15 by the board;
16 (e) Employ an executive director and fix his or her compensation. The executive
17 director shall serve at the pleasure of the board, administer the day-to-day
18 operations of the Office of the Kentucky Board of Dentistry, and supervise all
19 directives of the board. The executive director shall possess a baccalaureate
20 degree and shall have no less than five (5) years of experience in public
21 administration;
22 (f) Employ or contract with an attorney licensed to practice law in Kentucky and
23 fix his or her compensation. The attorney shall serve at the pleasure of the
24 board and have primary assignment to the board;
25 (g) Employ or contract with personnel sufficient to carry out the statutory
26 responsibilities of the board;
27 (h) Establish committees and subcommittees and the membership thereof.
