26 SECTION 11. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 313 IS CREATED TO
27 READ AS FOLLOWS:
Page 21 of 33
BR211000.100 - 2110 - XXXX 3/11/2026 2:43 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2110
1 (1) A person or entity shall not:
2 (a) Represent themselves by using the title dentist, dental specialist, dental
3 hygienist, or dental assistant unless licensed or registered under the
4 provisions of this chapter;
5 (b) Own, operate, offer to operate, or represent or advertise the operation of a
6 dental practice of any type unless licensed by or employing individuals
7 licensed by the board; or
8 (c) Employ a dentist, dental hygienist, or dental assistant unless that dentist,
9 dental hygienist, or dental assistant is licensed or registered under the
10 provisions of this chapter.
11 (2) In a clinical setting:
12 (a) A person or entity that is not licensed to practice dentistry under this
13 chapter shall not exercise control over:
14 1. Clinical decision making;
15 2. Diagnosis or treatment planning;
16 3. Patient records;
17 4. The selection or supervision of licensed dental personnel; or
18 5. The professional judgment of a licensed dentist; and
19 (b) A licensed dentist shall retain final authority and responsibility for all
20 clinical decisions affecting patient care.
21 (3) The clinical operations of a dental practice entity shall not be directly or
22 indirectly controlled by a person or entity that establishes reimbursement rates for
23 dental services.
24 (4) On or after the effective date of this Act, an entity that holds a controlling
25 ownership interest or exercises control over a dental practice under a
26 management or service contract may continue to hold the controlling ownership
27 interest or to exercise the control over the dental practice.
