1 (5) On or after the effective date of this Act, an entity that holds a controlling
2 ownership interest or exercises control over a dental practice under subsection (4)
3 of this section shall not:
4 (a) Acquire a controlling ownership interest in an additional entity that is a
5 dental practice;
6 (b) Increase its percentage of ownership of a dental practice if the increase
7 would result in a controlling ownership; or
8 (c) Expand the scope of control exercised over a dental practice.
9 (6) On or after the effective date of this Act, any material restructuring, merger,
10 transfer, or assignment resulting in a change in controlling ownership of a dental
11 practice shall be subject to the requirements of this section.
12 (7) This section shall apply prospectively and shall not impair or invalidate
13 ownership interests or contractual arrangements lawfully in existence on the
14 effective date of this Act.
