1 board in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A[ pursuant to this chapter], a practice
2 standard, or an order of the board.
3 (3) Each complaint shall:
4 (a) Be in writing;
5 (b) Identify specifically the person or organization against whom the complaint is
6 made;
7 (c) Set forth the facts relating to the violation alleged and any other supporting
8 information which may have a bearing on the matter;
9 (d) Contain the name, address, telephone number, facsimile number, and email[e-
10 mail] address, if available, of the complainant; and
11 (e) Be signed by the complainant as the truth of the statements contained in the
12 complaint by the complainant.
13 (4) A complaint which is unsigned shall not be acted upon by the executive director
14 unless the complaint involves a violation of standards set forth by the Centers for
15 Disease Control or alleged mental or physical impairment as provided for in KRS
16 313.130. A complaint which is not signed in the manner specified in subsection (3)
17 of this section shall be returned to the complainant for completion.
18 (5) The executive director of the board may, on behalf of the board, based on
19 knowledge available to the Office of the Board, make a complaint against any
20 person or organization regulated by the board in the same manner as provided in
21 subsection (3) of this section.
22 (6) Upon receipt of a properly completed complaint, the executive director shall assign
23 the complaint to a staff investigator who shall investigate the complaint and shall
24 make findings of fact and recommendations to the executive director who shall then
25 convene a meeting of the Law Enforcement Committee.
26 (7) The staff investigator shall notify the person or organization against whom the
27 complaint has been filed and shall notify the employer of the dentist, dental
Page 27 of 33
BR211000.100 - 2110 - XXXX 3/11/2026 2:43 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2110
1 hygienist, or dental assistant of the complaint.
2 (8) The notification shall name the person or organization complained against, the
3 complainant, the violations alleged, and the facts presented in the complaint and
4 shall notify the person or organization complained against and the employer of:
5 (a) The fact that the complaint shall be answered, the steps for answering the
6 complaint, and the action to be taken if the complaint is not answered;
7 (b) The timeframe and steps in the proceedings of a complaint;
8 (c) The rights of the parties, including the right to counsel; and
9 (d) The right to testify at any hearing.
10 (9) Upon the failure of a licensee or certificate holder to respond to a written accusation
11 or to request a hearing within twenty (20) days after the sending of the accusation,
12 the accused shall be considered to have admitted the truth of the facts and the
13 circumstances in the allegation and appropriate discipline may be imposed.
14 (10) After reviewing the complaint and results of any investigation conducted on behalf
15 of the board, the Law Enforcement Committee shall consider whether the
16 accusation is sufficient to remand the matter for a hearing as provided in this
17 section and KRS Chapter 13B. A majority vote of the members of the Law
18 Enforcement Committee shall be necessary for action to [either ]remand the matter
19 for hearing, offer a settlement, or dismiss the complaint without a hearing.
20 (11) If the Law Enforcement Committee dismisses the complaint, all parties notified
21 previously shall be notified of the action. If the Law Enforcement Committee
22 remands the matter for a hearing, all parties notified previously shall be notified of
23 the action.
24 (12) Each proceeding to consider the imposition of a penalty which the board is
25 authorized to impose pursuant to this chapter shall be conducted in accordance with
26 KRS Chapter 13B.
27 (13) A hearing panel for purposes of making a decision in any disciplinary matter shall
Page 28 of 33
BR211000.100 - 2110 - XXXX 3/11/2026 2:43 PM Jacketed

