1 consist of a quorum of the remaining seven (7) voting members of the board who
2 are not on the Law Enforcement Committee and the hearing officer.
3 (14) The board may issue subpoenas to compel the attendance of witnesses and the
4 production of documents in the conduct of an investigation. The subpoenas may be
5 enforced by any Circuit Court for contempt. Any order or subpoena of the court
6 requiring the attendance and testimony of witnesses and the production of
7 documentary evidence may be enforced and shall be valid anywhere in this state.
8 (15) At all hearings the board attorney or, on request of the board, the Attorney General
9 of this state or one (1) of the assistant attorneys general designated, shall appear and
10 represent the board.
11 (16) The dentist, dental hygienist, or dental assistant who is the defendant in a hearing
12 shall be a party to the action and may appear and testify in the matter at any
13 deposition or hearing on the matter and may propose conclusions of law, findings of
14 fact, and penalties to the hearing panel.
15 (17) To make a finding or impose discipline, a majority of the members of the hearing
16 panel who are not the hearing officer shall agree on the finding or discipline.
17 (18) The final order in any disciplinary proceeding shall be prepared by the hearing
18 officer and sent to all parties in the manner prescribed by law.
19 (19) Any person or entity aggrieved by a final order of the board may appeal the final
20 order to the Circuit Court of the county in which the person or entity resides in
21 accordance with KRS Chapter 13B.
22 (20) Upon final disposition of a complaint which results in disciplinary action, the final
23 order shall be published on the website[Web site] of the board, placed in the record
24 of the licensed or registered individual, and reported to the National Practitioner
